<section>
	<div class="terms-wrapper">
		<div class="section-gap">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="row">
					<div class="col-md-9">
					<h1 class="hd1 margin-t-0 margin-b-0 pad-b-20 text-center">Glossary</h1>
					<div class="row">
					<div class="col-sm-12">
						<div class="terms-description">
							
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
							<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
								<p class="decs-p-text">Action</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
								<p>It simply means a player has to act when the turn comes. If
									a player seems not realizing it&#8217;s his turn, the dealer will
									remind by saying &#8220;Your action, sir.&#8221; When a third
									heart hits the board, you have to assume someone has made a flush
									so a lot of action on the board.</p>
							</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
							<p class="decs-p-text">Ante</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12"><p>At the starting of the poker hand, a small bet is
									contributed by players to seed the pot. Ante is not used in
									usually Hold&#8217;em games; they use &#8220;blinds&#8221; to get
									initial money into the pot.</p>
							</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
								<p class="decs-p-text">All-In</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12"><p>Run out of all chips while betting or calling. A player
									can&#8217;t go into his pocket for more money during a hand if he
									runs out.</p>
							</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
								<p class="decs-p-text">Aggressive</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12"><p>A player tends to play aggressively large bets.</p>
							</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
								<p class="decs-p-text">Bad Beat</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12"><p>A large underdog beats a favoured hand. It generally
									means the winner of the pot had no chance of winning, but it was
									the shocking lucking that he managed to find that one card that
									would win the pot.</p>
							</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
								<p class="decs-p-text">Bet</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
							<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12"><p>Pre-flop, the small blind is the first chip placed in the
									pot. It is classified as the first bet.</p>
							</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Big Blind</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>It is the larger blind among the full first round bet.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Bluff</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>To bet or raise holding a hand weaker than the opponent to
									force them to fold their stronger hand.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Bottom Pair</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>The lowest card on the flop.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Call</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Amount of money puts into the pot that is equal to the most
									recent bet or raise.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Calling Station</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Calling station denotes to a weak and passive player who
									calls a lot but doesn&#8217;t raise or fold.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Calling Station</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>The beginning or primary pot created during a poker hand.
									It is opposed to one or more side pots created by
									one or more players when they go all-in.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Check</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>It prevents a player not to bet with a later option to call or
									raise.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Community Cards</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Cards that are presented face-up and shared with the
									players. These are also sometimes referred as board cards or "the
									board".</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Dealer</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>The player in the poker game who is involved in dealing the
									cards. When an automated dealer (online) is dealing the card it
									is necessary to identify who the player is because the betting
									action starts to the left of the dealer.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Draw</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>To play a bad hand but could become a good hand if the
									right cards come up.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Fast</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A player who aggressively bets fast and raise as
									much as possible.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Favourite</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A poker hand statistically favourite to win the game.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Flop</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>After the initial betting round, three cards are dealt face
									up in the centre of the table for every player. This is
									flop.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Fold</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Lay down your hand to forfeit any chance to win the current
									pot.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>	
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Free Roll</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>In this poker hand, one has a chance to win the pot but
									presently is tied with his opponent. For example, you have clubs
									of K-10 and your opponent has also hearts K-10. Now both are tied
									but the final card happens to be a club, your opponent will lose
									 your flush. There is no final card that will make your
									opponent win; only you can improve, so you are free rolling your
									opponent.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Gutshot</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A situation where the player is unable to make a straight, due to one missing card in the hand. </p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Jackpot</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>It is a type of a jackpot which is offered to a player, who has a good hand, but loses to another player with a better hand.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text"> Kicker</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>An unpaired card to determine two nearly equivalent hands.
									For example, you have A-K and your opponent has A-Q. Now if the
									river card has an ace in it, you both have a pair of aces but you
									have a king kicker, which is a stronger hand.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Limit Texas Hold&#8217;em</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>In this betting structure, the big blind is set as the
									standard amount of all bets and raises. The amount of the bets
									and raises increases to twice the big blind in the turn and river
									rounds. During each round, a player is permitted to place a bet
									and raise it only three times.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Maniac</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A player with highly aggressive playing method such as
									betting, bluffing and raising. A maniac is not a good player. He
									is simply a gambler, but a player who does occasionally maniac
									can be dangerous as it confuses the opponent.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Mixed Texas Hold&#8217;em</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Different rounds are played in accordance with different
									betting structures. Some rounds may be Limit Hold&#8217;em while
									others may be No Limit Hold&#8217;em.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">No Limit</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Different rounds are played in accordance with different
									betting structures. Some rounds may be Limit Hold&#8217;em while
									others may be No Limit Hold&#8217;em.</p>
									<p>For example, if a player bets an amount of say $15, then
									the next player has to raise by a minimum amount of $15, i.e, he
									makes a total bet of $30.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Offsuit</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A hold'em beginning hand with two cards of different suits.
								</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">One-Gap</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>
									Open-Ended Straight Draw <br> When you have holding for
									example, 9-8 with a board of 2-7-6, you will either seek 10 or 5
									to make it straight.
								</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Overcard</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-4">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A card higher than anything on the board. For example, you
									have AK and the flop comes Q-8-7, you can&#8217;t make a pair but
									have two overcards.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Pot</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A pot is a collective money that players bet during a single
									hand or game according to rules of the game. At the end of a
									hand, either by all but one player folding or by showdown, the
									pot is won by a single player or shared by players holding
									winning cards. In some occasions such as free-rolling, a pot can
									be split between two players. Also, pot can be shared in high-low
									games where not only the highest hand can win, but under the
									right conditions, the lowest hand will win a share of the pot.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Pre-Flop</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>After the hole cards are dealt, there is a round of betting
									depending on these hole cards. You can either check, bet or fold
									as per your judgment of your cards.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Pot Limit Texas Hold'em</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>The minimum amount for betting and raising is the same as
									in No Limit Hold&#8217;em. The maximum raise is limited to the
									total amount of the pot "the value of the active pot, all the
									bets on the table and the value that the player calls before
									playing, all taken together.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Quads</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>Four of a kind</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Ragged</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A flop that doesn&#8217;t help anybody too much. For
									example, a flop J-6-2 is considered ragged.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Rainbow</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-9 col-xs-12">
									<p>A flop that contains three different suits so no flush can
									be made.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
								<div class="col-md-2 col-xs-4">
									<p class="decs-p-text">Raise</p>
								</div>
								<div class="col-md-1 col-xs-8">
								<p class="decs-p-text">:</p>
							</div>
								<div class="col-md-12">
									<p>To increase the current bet.</p>
								</div>
							</div>
							</div>
							
							<div class="container-fluid">
								<div class="row">
